etiam forte circumfusae multitudinis compositi non ferunt illud intentionis silentium : nec sibi diserti videntur, nisi omnia tumultu et vociferatione concusserint—tot pariter ac tam nobiles etc.: The anaphoric ‘ cum ' clauses analyse the composition of the great audience which faced the orators of the Republic on important occasions. The higher (nobiles) and lower classes (clientelae, tribus), of the city and the representatives of municipalities crowded the foruni, and took a personal interest in court trials.
